Code of Conduct
Introduction
We are committed to creating an inclusive environment where everyone feels welcome and valued. This Code of Conduct outlines the expectations for behavior within our community.

Our Pledge
We pledge to make participation in our project a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion (or lack thereof), or sexual orientation.

Standards
Be Respectful: Treat others with kindness and respect.

Be Inclusive: Welcome diverse perspectives and contributions.

Be Open-Minded: Engage constructively with differing opinions.

Avoid Harassment: Refrain from any form of harassment or discriminatory behavior.

Reporting Incidents
If you encounter any unacceptable behavior or have concerns about this code being violated:

Contact us via Your Email Address or through GitHub issues.

Provide as much detail as possible about the incident.

We will address all incidents promptly and fairly.

Replace [Your Email Address](mailto:your.email@example.com) with your actual contact information if you want people to be able to reach out directly.
